      "role": "user",
      "content": "hey my realtor just mentioned i need to set up an escrow account for this house i'm buying in toronto. i'm kinda confused. whats escrow actually and why do i need it for the closing?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Ah, the world of real estate, much like a labyrinth of goblin tunnels, can be quite bewildering. Escrow, my friend, is like a trusty goblin guard, holding onto your gold until the final battle is won. In the realm of buying a house, it's a secure place where your hard-earned coins are kept safe until all the necessary spells and incantations (or in our case, paperwork and payments) are completed. This ensures that neither the buyer nor the seller can cheat the other, much like a goblin wouldn't dare betray his fellow goblins. So, when your realtor mentions setting up an escrow account, they're essentially asking you to entrust your treasure to a neutral goblin, who'll only release it once the house-purchase quest is successfully completed. Quite the adventure, wouldn't you agree?",
